memberOrga:
The Bussola Institute is an independent, not-for-profit, non-governmental research institute and, as such, does not have member organisations.  The institute has an Honorary Advisory Board (6 members) and a Board of Directors (2 members).  Membership is detailed on the institute's website.&#xd;
&#xd;
The Honorary Advisory Board members are:&#xd;
&#xd;
H E Jose Maria Aznar (Chairman Honorary Advisory Board), Former President of the Government of Spain&#xd;
&#xd;
HE Mary McAleese, Former President of Ireland&#xd;
 &#xd;
H E Anders Fogh Rasmussen, Former NATO Secretary General and former Prime Minister of Denmark&#xd;
 &#xd;
H E Jadranka Kosor, Former Prime Minister of the Republic of Croatia&#xd;
 &#xd;
H E Anna Diamantopoulou, Former EU Commissioner and former Minister (Greece)&#xd;
 &#xd;
H E François Fillon, Former Prime Minister of France&#xd;
&#xd;
The members of the Board of Directors are:&#xd;
&#xd;
H E Amal Al Haddabi, Founder, Chairperson of the Board of Directors&#xd;
&#xd;
H E Mohammed Baharoon, Founder, Member of the Board of Directors
